Hey, aren't you gonna go, no?

493
00:39:02,073 --> 00:39:03,734
I set him up, bro.

494
00:39:03,941 --> 00:39:06,432
I'm gonna let the guards do it for us.

495
00:39:13,851 --> 00:39:16,012
Go over there and spread out.

496
00:39:20,558 --> 00:39:21,582
Let's go, let's go!

497
00:39:23,461 --> 00:39:25,292
Check that gate.

498
00:39:27,665 --> 00:39:29,565
They're all locked.

499
00:39:33,804 --> 00:39:36,295
What do we have here?

500
00:39:36,841 --> 00:39:39,935
-Please. Please.
-So beautiful.

501
00:39:41,078 --> 00:39:42,375
You're so tender.

502
00:39:42,580 --> 00:39:44,377
Hey, big dog,
Rivera sent me to find you.

503
00:39:44,582 --> 00:39:46,550
Where'd you get
these fine little honeys at?

504
00:39:46,751 --> 00:39:49,015
-Back off, homes.
-Hey, there's two of them.

505
00:39:49,220 --> 00:39:50,710
You got that one, I got this one--

506
00:39:51,756 --> 00:39:55,055
<i>I told you to back off, mano.</i>

507
00:39:56,994 --> 00:39:59,428
Yeah, I got it. I got it.

508
00:39:59,630 --> 00:40:01,291
Bitch.

509
00:40:02,433 --> 00:40:06,028
<i>All right, ése.
We'll see what's up later, right?</i>

510
00:40:06,237 --> 00:40:07,761
See you.

511
00:40:10,107 --> 00:40:12,632
I have plans for both of you.

512
00:40:12,843 --> 00:40:14,504
Move!

513
00:40:27,425 --> 00:40:29,655
I could have handled that
all by myself back there.

514
00:40:29,860 --> 00:40:30,827
Yeah, right.

515
00:40:31,028 --> 00:40:34,691
As long as JT and everybody else
thinks I killed Angel, I'm a marked man.

516
00:40:34,899 --> 00:40:37,459
This way, they gotta shoot
their own brother to get to me.

517
00:40:37,668 --> 00:40:39,135
Man, these guys ain't my brothers.

518
00:40:39,336 --> 00:40:42,100
I told you before, Burke, I'm a loner.

519
00:40:42,840 --> 00:40:44,330
I don't care about no one.

520
00:40:44,708 --> 00:40:46,835
Just like you, man.

521
00:40:48,145 --> 00:40:51,012
-Come on.
-I got somebody I care about.

522
00:40:51,549 --> 00:40:53,915
You ladies picked
the wrong day to visit.

523
00:40:54,785 --> 00:40:58,585
You leave this room and you're dead.

524
00:41:05,596 --> 00:41:08,497
Oh, God, he locked us in.

525
00:41:08,699 --> 00:41:12,032
We're gonna have to stay calm.
We're gonna have to try and stay calm.

526
00:41:40,130 --> 00:41:41,563
Goddamn it.

527
00:41:42,399 --> 00:41:43,388
We lost power, warden.

528
00:41:43,601 --> 00:41:46,001
But we're switching
to emergency generators right now.

529
00:41:46,971 --> 00:41:48,905
What are you doing?
What are you doing?

530
00:41:49,106 --> 00:41:51,574
Trying to figure a way out of here.

531
00:41:52,109 --> 00:41:55,601
I saw on TV that the safest thing to do
at a time like this is to sit and wait.

532
00:41:55,813 --> 00:41:58,373
Are you crazy?
That is not the safest thing.

533
00:41:58,582 --> 00:42:01,346
Any minute that guy could be back
and shoot either one of us.

534
00:42:01,552 --> 00:42:03,577
If we do get out,
it might get us both killed.

535
00:42:03,787 --> 00:42:07,348
Well, you know what? You take your
chances here, I'll take mine out there.

536
00:42:07,558 --> 00:42:09,924
Let's say you do get out.
What-- What-- What then?

537
00:42:10,127 --> 00:42:11,594
There's a riot on the other side.

538
00:42:11,795 --> 00:42:15,060
Do you really think
you're gonna get out through that?

539
00:42:16,033 --> 00:42:17,694
-You have no idea--
-Shut up.

540
00:42:17,902 --> 00:42:19,563
What?

541
00:42:21,805 --> 00:42:22,772
Real smart.

542
00:42:22,973 --> 00:42:24,964
I don't think just because
you're big and tall...

543
00:42:25,175 --> 00:42:27,336
...that you can open that
without a key.

544
00:42:28,579 --> 00:42:32,538
You are just begging for me
to kick your ass, aren't you?

545
00:42:32,750 --> 00:42:34,843
Worse than the police, man.

546
00:42:35,052 --> 00:42:37,111
Get off me, man.
You make me nervous.

547
00:42:37,321 --> 00:42:40,256
-You got a bull's-eye on your back.
-I didn't kill Angel.

548
00:42:40,457 --> 00:42:42,857
-Well, who did, then?
-Cortez.

549
00:42:47,131 --> 00:42:49,292
Angel!

550
00:42:56,140 --> 00:42:58,040
-Cortez?
-Yeah.

551
00:42:58,242 --> 00:43:00,210
Oh, I get it.

552
00:43:00,411 --> 00:43:02,641
The riots, the distraction.

553
00:43:02,846 --> 00:43:06,282
Then you'll hook up with him later,
and y'all gonna fly off in the sunset.

554
00:43:06,483 --> 00:43:09,145
But not without me. I got value.
You take me with you.

555
00:43:09,353 --> 00:43:12,254
-You'll just slow me down.
-Slow you down?

556
00:43:12,456 --> 00:43:14,549
You the big meathead, motherfucker.

557
00:43:14,758 --> 00:43:16,623
-Burke!
-You--

558
00:43:17,494 --> 00:43:19,621
-Get in the cell--
-Relax. I don't wanna hurt you.

559
00:43:19,830 --> 00:43:21,764
-Get in the cell--
-Relax.

560
00:43:24,435 --> 00:43:25,402
Oh, fuck.

561
00:43:29,940 --> 00:43:31,339
Come on.

562
00:43:31,542 --> 00:43:33,305
Get them all locked in there.

563
00:43:37,181 --> 00:43:38,512
Burke, Burke, Burke.

564
00:43:42,386 --> 00:43:44,786
<i>-There's other juras I can hurt.
-That's right.</i>

565
00:43:45,189 --> 00:43:46,349
Let's go!

566
00:43:46,557 --> 00:43:48,889
-Come on!
-Okay, okay, come on.

567
00:43:51,495 --> 00:43:52,723
Bitch.

568
00:43:53,664 --> 00:43:55,325
Beat your ass.

569
00:43:55,833 --> 00:43:59,269
You know, my fiancé Bernard
could get this thing open in a second.

570
00:43:59,470 --> 00:44:01,028
He was a master thief.

571
00:44:01,238 --> 00:44:04,139
Real stupid, too.
Got himself caught up.

572
00:44:04,341 --> 00:44:07,276
I've been waiting for that man for years.

573
00:44:08,312 --> 00:44:11,179
What about you?
Who were you here to see?

574
00:44:12,316 --> 00:44:13,476
My dad.

575
00:44:14,918 --> 00:44:16,351
How long has he been in?

576
00:44:17,588 --> 00:44:19,146
Two years and four more to go.

577
00:44:23,494 --> 00:44:25,155
Let me try.

578
00:44:30,200 --> 00:44:33,761
Oh, goodness, I hope Bernard didn't go
get himself in no more trouble.

579
00:44:40,985 --> 00:44:43,419
-Would you look at that?
-They're dead.

580
00:44:44,889 --> 00:44:46,049
<i>-All units--!
-Hey, come on.</i>

581
00:44:46,257 --> 00:44:47,656
<i>--cell block C.</i>

582
00:44:47,858 --> 00:44:50,656
Get the walkie, man. It might--
Goddamn it!

583
00:44:51,395 --> 00:44:53,556
-Two guards are dead.
-Jesus.

584
00:44:53,764 --> 00:44:55,664
Surveillance confirms
both were last seen...

585
00:44:55,866 --> 00:44:58,528
...with the transfer from New Alcatraz
when the riot started.

586
00:45:01,639 --> 00:45:04,335
All officers fall back
behind the perimeter.

587
00:45:04,542 --> 00:45:08,308
Fall back behind the perimeter.
Meet at security checkpoints.

588
00:45:08,512 --> 00:45:09,877
You're clearing all cellblocks?

589
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:12,776
I'm pulling my men out
until they've all got body armor...

590
00:45:12,983 --> 00:45:14,644
...and something to fight back with.

591
00:45:14,852 --> 00:45:16,683
All officers, pull back.

592
00:45:16,887 --> 00:45:21,586
Convene in the armory for body armor
and riot gear for ERT response.

593
00:45:23,994 --> 00:45:25,427
Yes?

594
00:45:27,665 --> 00:45:29,656
-Sir.
-What?

595
00:45:29,867 --> 00:45:32,495
There's an inmate on line 101.

596
00:45:32,703 --> 00:45:35,831
-What?
-It's Alex Cortez.

597
00:45:38,876 --> 00:45:40,036
Put him through.

598
00:45:44,048 --> 00:45:47,575
Alex? Where are you?
What phone are you on?

599
00:45:47,785 --> 00:45:51,448
You don't get to ask questions.
You get to take orders.

600
00:45:51,655 --> 00:45:53,987
Or else more body bags
are coming out the front gate.

601
00:45:54,191 --> 00:45:56,751
If I find out you're responsible
for anyone's death--

602
00:45:56,961 --> 00:45:58,053
<i>Shut up, fool.</i>

603
00:45:58,729 --> 00:46:00,697
I'm doing life without parole.

604
00:46:00,898 --> 00:46:02,160
Don't threaten me again.

605
00:46:03,100 --> 00:46:06,467
-What phone is he on?
-It's impossible to tell.

606
00:46:06,670 --> 00:46:09,935
Here's what you're gonna do.
Call the governor.

607
00:46:10,140 --> 00:46:11,664
Tell him to get in his helicopter...

608
00:46:11,875 --> 00:46:14,139
...and fly his fat ass
out here immediately.

609
00:46:14,678 --> 00:46:17,442
I don't think I have the authority
to make that happen.

610
00:46:17,648 --> 00:46:19,980
If you can't, the hostages die.

611
00:46:20,484 --> 00:46:22,384
You have hostages?

612
00:46:22,586 --> 00:46:26,955
<i>Yeah. Two beautiful young ladies.</i>

613
00:46:27,324 --> 00:46:30,384
Not the kind of people you people
don't give a damn about.

614
00:46:30,594 --> 00:46:34,428
Make it happen, Wallace.
Don't forget the helicopter.

615
00:46:39,203 --> 00:46:42,570
Check the visitor records.
Find out if anyone is unaccounted for.

616
00:46:44,675 --> 00:46:46,870
-Get me the governor.
-Yes, sir, right away.

617
00:46:49,213 --> 00:46:52,205
Call the warden.
Get us the fuck out of here.

618
00:46:53,384 --> 00:46:55,113
We're in lockdown, governor.

619
00:46:55,319 --> 00:46:57,685
The two cellblocks
have been manually overridden.

620
00:46:57,888 --> 00:47:00,652
<i>-How is that possible?
-We're not exactly sure, sir.</i>

621
00:47:01,025 --> 00:47:04,517
It seems some inmates have gained
access to one of the control panels.

622
00:47:04,728 --> 00:47:05,717
What's their motive?

623
00:47:06,363 --> 00:47:10,026
It's gang-related. They're at war, sir.
Total chaos.

624
00:47:10,234 --> 00:47:11,360
Can you contain it?

625
00:47:11,769 --> 00:47:15,796
We're trying, sir. Emergency Response
Teams have been deployed.

626
00:47:16,006 --> 00:47:18,304
But there have been
some officer fatalities.

627
00:47:18,509 --> 00:47:21,910
Damn it, Wallace. I mean, it's the last
thing we need in an election year.

628
00:47:22,479 --> 00:47:26,006
-How many officers?
-Three that we know of for sure.

629
00:47:26,216 --> 00:47:30,414
All right. Look, you need to end this
thing quickly, no matter what it takes.

630
00:47:30,621 --> 00:47:33,556
<i>All right?
But protect our people at all cost.</i>

631
00:47:33,757 --> 00:47:34,985
<i>Has the press been notified?</i>

632
00:47:35,192 --> 00:47:37,524
No, sir. We've been able
to keep a lid on that.

633
00:47:37,928 --> 00:47:42,422
All right. My office will handle
all the press from this end.

634
00:47:42,633 --> 00:47:45,101
Just a minute. Charlie.
Hey, call the airport...

635
00:47:45,302 --> 00:47:48,271
...make sure the helicopter's ready,
wheels up in 20 minutes.

636
00:47:48,472 --> 00:47:50,372
We're going to Creighton.

637
00:47:50,574 --> 00:47:51,541
I'm on my way.

638
00:47:51,742 --> 00:47:53,334
Yes, sir.

639
00:48:00,517 --> 00:48:03,247
-Here we go.
-Tell me why you got transferred here.

640
00:48:03,821 --> 00:48:05,880
-Tell me.
-What, you don't know?

641
00:48:06,090 --> 00:48:08,752
-Bullshit about a fight.
-It was more than a fight.

642
00:48:08,959 --> 00:48:11,393
It's three of them and they thought
because I'm little...

643
00:48:11,628 --> 00:48:14,688
...I couldn't whoop that ass,
but I got this thing I did:

644
00:48:16,800 --> 00:48:18,859
-You can't fight worth a shit.
-Shut up.

645
00:48:19,069 --> 00:48:20,696
Kick your ass.

646
00:48:20,904 --> 00:48:23,372
-What?
-If my ankle didn't hurt.

647
00:48:24,041 --> 00:48:27,875
Hey, quit lying to me.
Why'd you get transferred here?

648
00:48:28,078 --> 00:48:32,640
I-- I wanted to be closer
to my fiancée, Cherise.

649
00:48:32,850 --> 00:48:35,148
-You're lying.
-No, I'm not.

650
00:48:35,352 --> 00:48:36,410
Your eyes are moving...

651
00:48:36,620 --> 00:48:38,611
-...and you're lying.
-My eyes always move.

652
00:48:38,822 --> 00:48:42,485
Yeah, that's my point exactly.
Why'd you get transferred here?

653
00:48:42,693 --> 00:48:44,388
Look, I can't swim.

654
00:48:44,895 --> 00:48:47,921
Creighton has no water or sharks.

655
00:48:48,132 --> 00:48:52,865
You're telling me you got transferred
here just so you could escape?

656
00:48:53,070 --> 00:48:56,870
Goddamn right.
I'm a crazy motherfucker.

657
00:48:59,610 --> 00:49:00,634
No shit.

658
00:49:03,180 --> 00:49:05,774
There's the motherfucker
that killed Angel.

659
00:49:07,117 --> 00:49:09,085
Hey, hey, hey. Wait, wait, wait!

660
00:49:21,465 --> 00:49:23,160
-Come on.
-Bitch!

661
00:49:24,735 --> 00:49:26,464
Any luck?

662
00:49:26,670 --> 00:49:28,467
It's not working.

663
00:49:28,872 --> 00:49:31,102
Just keep trying.

664
00:49:31,742 --> 00:49:33,369
Been trying.

665
00:49:34,611 --> 00:49:36,238
Look, we need another way.

666
00:49:36,446 --> 00:49:39,142
God knows when that guy
is gonna come back.

667
00:49:43,754 --> 00:49:45,619
This is creepy.

668
00:49:46,623 --> 00:49:48,454
It's where people watch
the executions.

669
00:49:48,659 --> 00:49:50,126
Yeah.

670
00:49:50,327 --> 00:49:53,057
-I could never do it.
-Do what?

671
00:49:53,463 --> 00:49:56,125
Just sit there and watch people die.

672
00:49:59,837 --> 00:50:02,305
We gotta get this door open.
It's our only way out.

673
00:50:18,755 --> 00:50:20,780
You tried to get out?

674
00:50:21,391 --> 00:50:24,292
After what we just said to you?

675
00:50:30,601 --> 00:50:32,330
Tie her up.

676
00:50:33,804 --> 00:50:35,669
What the hell is wrong with you?

677
00:50:37,574 --> 00:50:41,704
I said, tie her up.

678
00:50:59,196 --> 00:51:01,596
It's too much like Alcatraz.

679
00:51:02,266 --> 00:51:04,826
Eric, make sure each officer gets one.

680
00:51:05,035 --> 00:51:08,300
Robert, back to the office
and monitor everything from there.

681
00:51:08,505 --> 00:51:11,668
All right, everybody. Time to move.

682
00:51:13,944 --> 00:51:17,072
All officers,
this is the warden speaking.

683
00:51:17,281 --> 00:51:20,614
<i>Take back control
one cellblock at a time.</i>

684
00:51:20,817 --> 00:51:23,251
<i>There's some inmates
to be on the lookout for.</i>

685
00:51:23,453 --> 00:51:27,253
<i>One William Burke.
One Bernard ''Twitch'' Washington.</i>

686
00:51:27,457 --> 00:51:29,618
<i>Both suspects
in the murder of two guards.</i>

687
00:51:29,826 --> 00:51:31,054
Did he just say my name?

688
00:51:31,929 --> 00:51:34,124
<i>Twitch is the transfer
from New Alcatraz.</i>

689
00:51:34,331 --> 00:51:36,458
<i>Both he and Burke
are likely armed.</i>

690
00:51:36,667 --> 00:51:38,498
No, no, we ain't, man.
Tell him we're not.

691
00:51:38,702 --> 00:51:40,602
<i>Try to take them alive.</i>

692
00:51:40,804 --> 00:51:42,738
<i>-Shoot to kill if you have to.
-Give me that.</i>

693
00:51:42,940 --> 00:51:46,467
-Man, you ain't talking to him.
-Look, I've gotta clear my name, Burke.

694
00:51:47,411 --> 00:51:49,845
We've got another situation
we gotta handle.

695
00:51:50,047 --> 00:51:53,915
Another inmate, Alex Cortez,
has taken hostages inside.

696
00:51:54,117 --> 00:51:55,516
We don't know exactly
how many...

697
00:51:55,719 --> 00:51:59,018
...but we believe
there are two missing visitors.

698
00:51:59,222 --> 00:52:01,816
-One Cherise--
-Hey, man, give me this thing.

699
00:52:02,025 --> 00:52:03,185
Wallace.

700
00:52:03,393 --> 00:52:04,985
-You there?
-Who's this?

701
00:52:05,195 --> 00:52:06,594
This is Twitch, man.

702
00:52:06,797 --> 00:52:08,788
Just what the hell
do you think you're doing?

703
00:52:08,999 --> 00:52:13,299
Hey, man, why you got this APB
out on me, man? I ain't kill nobody.

704
00:52:13,503 --> 00:52:15,164
No one's accused you of anything.

705
00:52:15,672 --> 00:52:18,140
Yeah, you did. You got the APB
cracking on us, man.

706
00:52:18,675 --> 00:52:21,143
<i>Rioters everywhere, man.
That's not due process.</i>

707
00:52:21,345 --> 00:52:24,781
Okay, then turn yourself in
and let's clear this up.

708
00:52:26,650 --> 00:52:28,675
-What? What is it?
-We're not meeting him.

709
00:52:28,885 --> 00:52:31,979
<i>-Twitch, are you there?
-Yeah, man.</i>

710
00:52:32,189 --> 00:52:34,714
Well, what do you say?
About going over this face to face?

711
00:52:36,326 --> 00:52:37,520
I know how that one works.

712
00:52:37,728 --> 00:52:39,787
We get there
and all your guard dogs are there.

713
00:52:39,997 --> 00:52:41,794
<i>You can forget that one, buddy.</i>

714
00:52:41,999 --> 00:52:44,058
My men won't harm you, I promise.

715
00:52:45,102 --> 00:52:47,502
Man, you gonna call the APB off
or what, Wallace?

716
00:52:47,704 --> 00:52:50,070
Just tell me where you are
and we'll work this--

717
00:52:50,273 --> 00:52:51,865
You're not gonna meet with him.

718
00:52:52,109 --> 00:52:54,703
Man, this is bullshit.
This prison's full of shit.

719
00:52:56,346 --> 00:52:57,313
Twitch?

720
00:53:02,185 --> 00:53:05,780
Twitch. Goddamn it, let's go.

721
00:53:05,989 --> 00:53:07,752
Open it.

722
00:53:14,598 --> 00:53:19,968
<i>The second hostage is Ellie Burke,
daughter of inmate William Burke.</i>

723
00:53:27,310 --> 00:53:30,871
Keep your eyes right. Move it out.
Keep your eyes right. Move it.

724
00:53:42,092 --> 00:53:44,253
<i>Hey, perro. Look at this.
Handle it.</i>

725
00:53:44,461 --> 00:53:46,361
Hurry up, men. Hurry up.

726
00:53:51,268 --> 00:53:52,758
Where's Burke?

727
00:53:52,969 --> 00:53:54,436
I don't know.

728
00:53:55,405 --> 00:53:58,533
-Are you sure?
-I don't give a damn about Burke.

729
00:53:58,742 --> 00:54:01,768
-You, motherfu--
-Wow, easy, easy. Easy.

730
00:54:04,414 --> 00:54:05,745
Is that right?

731
00:54:05,949 --> 00:54:07,041
<i>Where's your jefe?</i>

732
00:54:07,350 --> 00:54:09,011
