in solitary, pulling a stunt like that.

1047
01:20:32,134 --> 01:20:36,036
Burke, Twitch, let's go.

1048
01:20:36,838 --> 01:20:38,897
-Let's go inside.
-Dad.

1049
01:20:40,442 --> 01:20:42,467
It's gonna be all right, baby.

1050
01:20:42,678 --> 01:20:45,169
-I love you.
-I love you.

1051
01:20:47,416 --> 01:20:49,907
I'm getting out soon, now, you hear?

1052
01:20:50,952 --> 01:20:53,352
-You wait for me, now.
-I always do.

1053
01:20:55,424 --> 01:20:56,948
Let's go.

1054
01:21:02,864 --> 01:21:04,263
Let's go.

1055
01:21:08,437 --> 01:21:12,100
And every word of it's true. I swear.

1056
01:21:12,307 --> 01:21:14,104
Just ask the warden.

1057
01:21:15,010 --> 01:21:20,971
I can verify that Bernard Washington
did in fact try to defuse the riot...

1058
01:21:21,183 --> 01:21:25,449
...and is one of two men responsible
for the rescue of the hostages.

1059
01:21:25,654 --> 01:21:27,622
The other one was Burke.

1060
01:21:27,823 --> 01:21:29,620
He helped with the saving thing too.

1061
01:21:29,825 --> 01:21:33,090
I remind you again that this is
your parole hearing, not Mr. Burke's.

1062
01:21:33,295 --> 01:21:35,263
I know. I just wanted
to put that on record.

1063
01:21:35,464 --> 01:21:39,366
For when it's his turn
to spin that parole wheel.

1064
01:21:39,568 --> 01:21:41,229
You sure about what you saw?

1065
01:21:44,673 --> 01:21:47,039
Well, we've heard the account
of your supposed bravery...

1066
01:21:47,242 --> 01:21:48,300
...from Warden Wallace.

1067
01:21:48,510 --> 01:21:50,034
And we've taken
into consideration...

1068
01:21:50,245 --> 01:21:52,270
...the years you've served
in New Alcatraz.

1069
01:21:52,481 --> 01:21:56,542
Except for a few minor infractions.

1070
01:21:57,452 --> 01:22:00,546
And we hereby grant you your parole.

1071
01:22:03,859 --> 01:22:05,827
Are you serious?

1072
01:22:07,395 --> 01:22:10,626
Thank you. Thank you.

1073
01:22:18,140 --> 01:22:20,370
Thank you, thank you.

1074
01:22:20,575 --> 01:22:22,133
-Congratulations, Twitch.
-Thank you.

1075
01:22:22,344 --> 01:22:24,835
-Good luck, man.
-Yeah.

1076
01:22:25,313 --> 01:22:27,213
Now keep that nose clean.

1077
01:22:27,415 --> 01:22:29,645
Ain't got to worry about me.

1078
01:22:31,219 --> 01:22:33,710
Bernard. Bernard!

1079
01:22:36,691 --> 01:22:39,023
Okay. I mean, come on.

1080
01:22:39,227 --> 01:22:41,661
Really, I ain't got no time for games.
What's up?

1081
01:22:41,863 --> 01:22:43,763
-Where is it?
-Just--

1082
01:22:43,965 --> 01:22:46,058
I see that big old box,
where is the gold?

1083
01:22:46,268 --> 01:22:48,395
-I don't see it.
-Shut up and just help me.

1084
01:22:48,603 --> 01:22:50,798
Help you? You big enough
to help yourself.

1085
01:22:51,006 --> 01:22:52,439
Just grab it. Ready?

1086
01:22:52,641 --> 01:22:55,041
Here we go.

1087
01:22:57,212 --> 01:22:59,442
-Oh, my God.
-Shit.

1088
01:22:59,648 --> 01:23:01,980
-Baby. Is it--?
-Shit.

1089
01:23:02,184 --> 01:23:06,211
It's gold. It's really here, baby.

1090
01:23:07,122 --> 01:23:09,215
You did it. Baby.

1091
01:23:09,424 --> 01:23:12,723
I can't believe it. You did it.

1092
01:23:14,563 --> 01:23:16,531
Twitch.

1093
01:23:19,534 --> 01:23:21,729
Twitch.

1094
01:23:27,809 --> 01:23:31,142
-We rich, baby.
-We rich. We rich.

1095
01:23:33,215 --> 01:23:36,844
-What?
-We better get this out of here quick.

1096
01:23:37,219 --> 01:23:39,153
-Look at this.
-Let me count my money.

1097
01:23:39,921 --> 01:23:42,253
-Oh, it's your money, Bernard?
-Yeah, it's my money.

1098
01:23:42,457 --> 01:23:43,754
That's what I'm talking about.

1099
01:23:43,959 --> 01:23:45,927
Just bring the money to the car.
Hurry up.

1100
01:23:46,127 --> 01:23:48,891
-You wouldn't help me dig, wouldn't--
-I ain't helping nothing.

1101
01:23:49,097 --> 01:23:51,429
When you was in the jail,
you was crying like girl.

1102
01:23:51,633 --> 01:23:53,567
I risked my life for you
and you wouldn't help.

1103
01:23:53,768 --> 01:23:54,996
Help me get this out of here.

1104
01:23:55,203 --> 01:23:57,068
Get your ass back here.

1105
01:24:01,376 --> 01:24:04,106
-Dude, you look tight.
-Thanks, this is my Snoop Dogg look.

1106
01:24:04,312 --> 01:24:07,213
I'm gonna tell you something.
You put this in your pocket, right?

1107
01:24:07,415 --> 01:24:09,645
Don't give it to your ma or pa
and don't buy no drugs.

1108
01:24:09,851 --> 01:24:12,684
You'll be all right. Go on, now.
You enjoy yourself, boy.

1109
01:24:12,888 --> 01:24:14,583
-Hey.
-Hey, Twitch. Hey, Cherise.

1110
01:24:14,789 --> 01:24:16,347
Hey, Burke.

1111
01:24:16,558 --> 01:24:18,048
What's up?

1112
01:24:18,260 --> 01:24:20,524
Same old, man. How about you?

1113
01:24:20,929 --> 01:24:23,591
You don't notice nothing different
about your boy?

1114
01:24:23,798 --> 01:24:25,459
You know, come to think of it...

1115
01:24:25,667 --> 01:24:28,363
...you are a hell of a lot uglier.

1116
01:24:28,670 --> 01:24:31,332
-Not funny. What you laughing at?
-Very funny.

1117
01:24:31,539 --> 01:24:34,975
If 80 million will make you this ugly,
you need a facelift.

1118
01:24:35,176 --> 01:24:37,201
-Only 80?
-Well, actually it was more.

1119
01:24:37,412 --> 01:24:39,346
We put the other 80
into a separate account.

1120
01:24:39,547 --> 01:24:41,845
-For you.
-Eighty million?

1121
01:24:42,050 --> 01:24:45,884
-Well, shit. It wasn't my idea.
-Yes, it was. Stop lying.

1122
01:24:46,087 --> 01:24:48,612
Eighty million dollars?

1123
01:24:48,823 --> 01:24:51,348
You gotta keep that on the low,
they might think I stole it.

1124
01:24:51,559 --> 01:24:53,117
Keep it on the low.

1125
01:24:53,328 --> 01:24:56,126
-I don't know what to say, guys.
-We owed you, Burke.

1126
01:24:56,331 --> 01:24:58,196
You make sure you push
some of that up, now.

1127
01:24:58,400 --> 01:25:02,131
You got that beautiful little daughter
of yours. Now, college is a killer.

1128
01:25:02,470 --> 01:25:05,268
Don't you worry, guys. I will.

1129
01:25:05,473 --> 01:25:08,965
-You gonna be okay in here?
-I'm gonna be just fine, darling.

1130
01:25:09,177 --> 01:25:10,610
